==Introduction==
The '''Boolean Property Type''' represents a boolean value (True/False).

The Wiki Automation Tool supports editing, viewing and searching on the Boolean properties.


==Definition==

The Boolean Property extends a common definition of the [[Help:Property|Property Definition]] with the following elements:

<pre>
<property ... labelTrue="{LABEL TRUE}" labelFalse="{LABEL FALSE}">

</property>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {LABEL TRUE}
| A label to be displayed for value: true.
|-
! {LABEL FALSE}
| A label to be displayed for value: false.
|}


==Semantic database==
The Boolean Property is implemented as a [[Special:Types/Boolean]] MediaWiki datatype.


==Example==
<pre>
<property name="Active" type="Boolean" label="Active" attribute="active" labelTrue="Active" labelFalse="Not active">
  <description>An Active is a boolean flag indicating a status of given entity.</description>
</property>
</pre>


==User Interface==
* '''View Page'''
The property displays a label associated with the Boolean value.

* '''Edit Page'''
The property provides a Checkbox input field to select Boolean value.

* '''Search Page'''
The property provides a RadioBox input field to select a desired search filter (including 'Not defined/Empty' value).
